dcterms:description: A large-scale and high-quality benchmark dataset for hierarchical few-shot object detection (Hi-FSOD), containing 176,350 wild-bird images across 1,432 categories organized into a 4-level taxonomy: 32 orders, 132 families, 572 genera, and 1,432 species. The dataset includes high-quality annotated bounding boxes and textual descriptions for each category, facilitating zero-shot object detection tasks and aiding in the monitoring and protection of endangered birds.
dcterms:title: HiFSOD-Bird
